
# Story-attachment directory. By default the directory is excluded so generated
# scratch content cannot leak into commits; specific files that the workstream
# needs under version control are added back via the explicit negation pattern
# below. The file-level `*` form (not the whole-directory form) is required so
# git recurses into the directory to evaluate the negations.
.forge-attachments/*

# Stage 5.1 user-stories reference, pinned under version control so the code,
# the planning artifacts in docs/stories/qq-MICROSOFT-TEAMS-MESS/, and the
# story-attachment reference document evolve together. The operator's upload
# pipeline may overwrite this file at any time; the operator-supplied copy is
# the canonical version when both exist.
!.forge-attachments/agent_swarm_messenger_user_stories.md

# .NET build output
[Bb]in/
[Oo]bj/

# .NET test/coverage artifacts
[Tt]est[Rr]esults/
*.coverage
*.coveragexml
coverage.*.xml
coverage.json
*.trx

# User-specific Visual Studio files
*.user
*.suo
.vs/

# Rider / ReSharper
.idea/
*.DotSettings.user

# Misc
*.swp
*.swo

# Teams sideload package output
src/AgentSwarm.Messaging.Teams/Manifest/bin/

.forge/
